New Records: Shohei Ohtani became the first player in MLB history to have 43 home runs and 43 stolen bases in a single season.
Shohei Ohtani surpassed Alex Rodriguez as the fastest to reach 43 home runs and 43 stolen bases, doing so in 126 games, the quickest in major-league history.
Key Match Events: Shohei Ohtani hit a solo home run in the eighth inning, a 380-foot shot that gave the Dodgers a 10-5 lead.
Shohei Ohtani stole a base in the second inning, becoming the first player in MLB history with 43 stolen bases in a single season.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Los Angeles Dodgers defeated the Arizona Diamondbacks with a final score of 10-9.
